{
  "methodology_version": "v1.8",
  "_meta": {
    "owner": "msi:openarx-methodist (content source-of-truth)",
    "schema": "methodist_framework_v2.md §5 (procedures/steps/gate/route); door surface §3 (focus? on diagnose/course)",
    "prompt_bodies": "design/methodist_v2/door_prompts.md (by door id) — Core lifts executable bodies from there; kept DRY, must stay in sync",
    "primitives": "all v1; names = framework §6 vocabulary; wired by (id, version)",
    "core_sync_needed": "exact I/O form of state-primitives finalized in Phase 2 against the live graph. Slot names aligned to Core's confirmed target column (tickets ...-0588/0589).",
    "gated_disabled": "dedup-detect composition present in framework §6 but GATED (Vlad's standing requirement — own trial before autonomous). NOT wired into the live checkpoint publish path this wave.",
    "confirmed_semantics": {
      "verdict_branch": "write-graph-records branches internally on verdict: GO → scientific claim + quality-stamp; RETURN → path/fact only (attempt+why), NOT a claim. Upstream transforms run unconditionally (§5.4).",
      "update_run_state": "one primitive, variant params, branch-by-data internally (verdict=GO → go_mark+advance; RETURN → no go_mark; status→set).",
      "create_corrective_activity": "RESERVED for supersede-of-published-claim (GO refinement of a prior claim; immutability add+link §7 inv-6), input from apply-supersede-guards — NOT fired on RETURN (RETURN corrections live in the checkpoint_return outcome-activity's activity_content). Dormant in the live checkpoint this wave (tied to gated dedup/supersede). ticket ...-0597.",
      "vectorize_and_store": "no-op on RETURN (no claim → no vector), branch-by-data-null. [confirm Core]",
      "update_dossier_mapping": "derives delta from verdict+tier_signal: autonomy_by_context[cycle] ONLY from verdict.next_dose.autonomy.level (carrier judgment, never GO-count); tier_by_context[creative_element]=tier_signal.target_tier (only when probe fired); passed_units+=unit on GO-with-unit; corrections_history RETURN→not_yet / GO→mark-applied; patches_received+=verdict.patches.",
      "update_dossier_mapping_ownership": "These rules are METHODOLOGY-OWNED POLICY, not primitive-intrinsic (framework §6: primitives are methodology-agnostic). v1: Core hardwires them into update-dossier for the single methodology (YAGNI, ticket ...-0590/0591). Target form: params-driven (rules as methodology params → generic flat-map writer). This _meta block is the SOURCE OF TRUTH for the rules; changing them is a methodology patch (methods-council), not a primitive change. Lift to params on the second methodology.",
      "dose_storage": "property of the run node (Neo4j); current dose only; dose history = immutable journal activities.",
      "agent_id_credential_id": "diagnose input agent_id maps to create-run credential_id (one entity) — confirm no lookup needed [Core]."
    }
  },
  "procedures": [
    {
      "name": "diagnose",
      "trigger": {
        "kind": "endpoint",
        "ref": "diagnose"
      },
      "steps": [
        {
          "id": "dossier",
          "primitive": "fetch-dossier",
          "version": "v1",
          "in": {
            "credential_id": "$input.agent_id"
          },
          "out": "dossier"
        },
        {
          "id": "run",
          "primitive": "create-run",
          "version": "v1",
          "in": {
            "credential_id": "$input.agent_id",
            "parent_run_id": "$input.payload.parent_run_id"
          },
          "out": "run"
        },
        {
          "id": "ctx",
          "primitive": "prepare-context",
          "version": "v1",
          "params": {
            "prompt": "diagnose"
          },
          "in": {
            "intent": "$input.payload.intent",
            "focus": "$input.payload.focus",
            "dossier_map": "$dossier.map"
          },
          "out": "ctx"
        },
        {
          "id": "diag",
          "primitive": "call-model",
          "version": "v1",
          "params": {
            "output_schema": "diagnose_out",
            "model": "gemini-3.1-pro-preview"
          },
          "in": {
            "context": "$ctx"
          },
          "out": "diag"
        },
        {
          "id": "persist",
          "primitive": "update-run-state",
          "version": "v1",
          "in": {
            "run_id": "$run.run_id",
            "stage": {
              "const": 1
            },
            "cycle": "$diag.cycle",
            "dose": "$diag.dose"
          }
        },
        {
          "id": "jrnl",
          "primitive": "append-journal",
          "version": "v1",
          "in": {
            "run_id": "$run.run_id",
            "event": {
              "const": "diagnose"
            },
            "payload": {
              "intent": "$input.payload.intent",
              "diagnosis": "$diag"
            }
          }
        }
      ],
      "outcome_from": "diag",
      "route": {
        "default": {
          "run_id": "$run.run_id",
          "dose": "$diag.dose",
          "rationale": "$diag.rationale"
        }
      }
    },
    {
      "name": "checkpoint",
      "trigger": {
        "kind": "endpoint",
        "ref": "checkpoint"
      },
      "_note": "Core of the protocol. Deterministic guards are early gates. Model call produces the two-axis verdict. Publish path folds in, driven by verdict (§4). Persist runs unconditionally (branch by data). dedup-detect NOT wired (gated).",
      "steps": [
        {
          "id": "idem",
          "primitive": "check-idempotency",
          "version": "v1",
          "in": {
            "run_id": "$input.run_id",
            "stage": "$input.payload.stage",
            "submission_hash": "$input.payload.submission_hash"
          },
          "out": "idem",
          "gate": {
            "when": "$idem.hit",
            "outcome": "idempotent"
          }
        },
        {
          "id": "runpath",
          "primitive": "fetch-run-path",
          "version": "v1",
          "in": {
            "run_id": "$input.run_id"
          },
          "out": "runpath"
        },
        {
          "id": "stop",
          "primitive": "check-stop-rule",
          "version": "v1",
          "in": {
            "path_events": "$runpath.path_events",
            "stage": "$input.payload.stage"
          },
          "out": "stop",
          "gate": {
            "when": "$stop.prev_not_go",
            "outcome": "prev_stage_not_go"
          }
        },
        {
          "id": "lang",
          "primitive": "detect-language",
          "version": "v1",
          "in": {
            "records": "$input.payload.submission.records"
          },
          "out": "lang",
          "gate": {
            "when": "$lang.non_english",
            "outcome": "non_english_rejected"
          }
        },
        {
          "id": "runst",
          "primitive": "fetch-run-state",
          "version": "v1",
          "in": {
            "run_id": "$input.run_id"
          },
          "out": "runst"
        },
        {
          "id": "dossier",
          "primitive": "fetch-dossier",
          "version": "v1",
          "in": {
            "credential_id": "$input.agent_id"
          },
          "out": "dossier"
        },
        {
          "id": "xcheck",
          "primitive": "crosscheck-tool-usage",
          "version": "v1",
          "in": {
            "run_id": "$input.run_id",
            "claimed_usage": "$input.payload.claimed_usage"
          },
          "out": "xcheck"
        },
        {
          "id": "ctx",
          "primitive": "prepare-context",
          "version": "v1",
          "params": {
            "prompt": "checkpoint"
          },
          "in": {
            "submission": "$input.payload.submission",
            "dose": "$runst.dose",
            "dossier_map": "$dossier.map",
            "crosscheck": "$xcheck"
          },
          "out": "ctx"
        },
        {
          "id": "verdict",
          "primitive": "call-model",
          "version": "v1",
          "params": {
            "output_schema": "checkpoint_verdict",
            "model": "gemini-3.1-pro-preview"
          },
          "in": {
            "context": "$ctx"
          },
          "out": "verdict"
        },
        {
          "id": "resolved",
          "primitive": "resolve-local-ids",
          "version": "v1",
          "in": {
            "submission": "$input.payload.submission",
            "verdict": "$verdict"
          },
          "out": "resolved"
        },
        {
          "id": "validated",
          "primitive": "validate-schema",
          "version": "v1",
          "in": {
            "records": "$resolved"
          },
          "out": "validated",
          "params": {
            "schema_ref": "layer2_v12"
          }
        },
        {
          "id": "vctx",
          "primitive": "prepare-context",
          "version": "v1",
          "params": {
            "prompt": "verify"
          },
          "in": {
            "records": "$resolved"
          },
          "out": "vctx"
        },
        {
          "id": "vstatus",
          "primitive": "call-model",
          "version": "v1",
          "params": {
            "output_schema": "verify_out",
            "model": "gemini-3.1-pro-preview"
          },
          "in": {
            "context": "$vctx"
          },
          "out": "vstatus"
        },
        {
          "id": "canon",
          "primitive": "canonicalize",
          "version": "v1",
          "in": {
            "records": "$resolved"
          },
          "out": "canon",
          "params": {
            "hash_scope": "frame_default"
          }
        },
        {
          "id": "guarded",
          "primitive": "apply-supersede-guards",
          "version": "v1",
          "in": {
            "records": "$canon"
          },
          "out": "guarded"
        },
        {
          "id": "hash",
          "primitive": "compute-hash",
          "version": "v1",
          "in": {
            "records": "$canon"
          },
          "out": "hash"
        },
        {
          "id": "written",
          "primitive": "write-graph-records",
          "version": "v1",
          "in": {
            "records": "$guarded",
            "verdict": "$verdict",
            "verify_status": "$vstatus",
            "language": "$lang",
            "hash": "$hash",
            "track_note": "$input.payload.submission.track_note",
            "credential_id": "$input.agent_id",
            "run_id": "$input.run_id",
            "stage": "$input.payload.stage",
            "cycle": "$runst.cycle"
          },
          "_note": "assembles the outcome-activity (checkpoint_go|checkpoint_return) carrying activity_content{run_id, stage, cycle_context, quality (GO), reasons+corrections (RETURN), track_note (both)}; GO also writes annotated scientific claims; RETURN writes only the outcome-activity (no claim).",
          "out": "written"
        },
        {
          "id": "committed",
          "primitive": "commit-bundle-atomic",
          "version": "v1",
          "in": {
            "written": "$written"
          },
          "out": "committed"
        },
        {
          "id": "vec",
          "primitive": "vectorize-and-store",
          "version": "v1",
          "in": {
            "committed": "$committed"
          },
          "out": "vec"
        },
        {
          "id": "rstate",
          "primitive": "update-run-state",
          "version": "v1",
          "in": {
            "run_id": "$input.run_id",
            "stage": "$input.payload.stage",
            "verdict": "$verdict",
            "next_dose": "$verdict.next_dose"
          }
        },
        {
          "id": "dwrite",
          "primitive": "update-dossier",
          "version": "v1",
          "in": {
            "credential_id": "$input.agent_id",
            "verdict": "$verdict",
            "tier_signal": "$verdict.tier_signal",
            "cycle": "$runst.cycle",
            "creative_element": "$runst.dose.probe.creative_element",
            "unit_id": "$runst.dose.unit_id",
            "unit_level": "$runst.dose.unit_level"
          }
        }
      ],
      "outcome_from": "verdict",
      "route": {
        "GO": {
          "verdict": {
            "const": "GO"
          },
          "next_dose": "$verdict.next_dose",
          "reasons": "$verdict.reasons"
        },
        "RETURN": {
          "verdict": {
            "const": "RETURN"
          },
          "reasons": "$verdict.reasons",
          "corrections": "$verdict.corrections"
        },
        "idempotent": {
          "outcome": "$idem.outcome.verdict",
          "reasons": "$idem.outcome.reasons",
          "corrections": "$idem.outcome.corrections",
          "ref": "$idem.outcome.ref"
        },
        "prev_stage_not_go": {
          "error": {
            "const": "prev_stage_not_go"
          },
          "missing": "$stop.missing"
        },
        "non_english_rejected": {
          "error": {
            "const": "non_english_rejected"
          },
          "reason": {
            "const": "submission contains non-English text — resubmit in English"
          },
          "detected_lang": "$lang.non_english_lang"
        }
      }
    },
    {
      "name": "ask",
      "trigger": {
        "kind": "endpoint",
        "ref": "ask"
      },
      "_note": "MERGED course+consult (single-door route, §3). Mid-stage guidance/clarification within the CURRENT cycle-stage dose; frame-anchored (cycle/stage prominent, anti-drift). MAY emit a dose_adjustment (course-mode, data-driven) or answer as pure clarification (consult-mode). NEVER advances the stage; never does the mentee's work (boundary 1). update-run-state applies dose_adjustment branch-by-data (no-op when absent → consult-mode leaves state unchanged).",
      "steps": [
        {
          "id": "runst",
          "primitive": "fetch-run-state",
          "version": "v1",
          "in": {
            "run_id": "$input.run_id"
          },
          "out": "runst"
        },
        {
          "id": "dossier",
          "primitive": "fetch-dossier",
          "version": "v1",
          "in": {
            "credential_id": "$input.agent_id"
          },
          "out": "dossier"
        },
        {
          "id": "ctx",
          "primitive": "prepare-context",
          "version": "v1",
          "params": {
            "prompt": "ask"
          },
          "in": {
            "question": "$input.payload.question",
            "focus": "$input.payload.focus",
            "cycle": "$runst.cycle",
            "stage": "$runst.stage",
            "dose": "$runst.dose",
            "dossier_map": "$dossier.map"
          },
          "out": "ctx"
        },
        {
          "id": "out",
          "primitive": "call-model",
          "version": "v1",
          "params": {
            "output_schema": "ask_out",
            "model": "gemini-3.1-pro-preview"
          },
          "in": {
            "context": "$ctx"
          },
          "out": "out"
        },
        {
          "id": "adj",
          "primitive": "update-run-state",
          "version": "v1",
          "in": {
            "run_id": "$input.run_id",
            "dose_adjustment": "$out.dose_adjustment",
            "advance_stage": {
              "const": false
            }
          }
        },
        {
          "id": "jrnl",
          "primitive": "append-journal",
          "version": "v1",
          "in": {
            "run_id": "$input.run_id",
            "event": {
              "const": "ask"
            },
            "payload": "$out"
          }
        }
      ],
      "outcome_from": "out",
      "route": {
        "default": {
          "answer": "$out.answer",
          "dose_adjustment": "$out.dose_adjustment"
        }
      }
    },
    {
      "name": "get_current_dose",
      "trigger": {
        "kind": "endpoint",
        "ref": "get_current_dose"
      },
      "_note": "deterministic, no model — session-death recovery",
      "steps": [
        {
          "id": "runst",
          "primitive": "fetch-run-state",
          "version": "v1",
          "in": {
            "run_id": "$input.run_id"
          },
          "out": "runst"
        },
        {
          "id": "runpath",
          "primitive": "fetch-run-path",
          "version": "v1",
          "in": {
            "run_id": "$input.run_id"
          },
          "out": "runpath"
        },
        {
          "id": "runclose",
          "primitive": "fetch-run-closeout",
          "version": "v1",
          "in": {
            "run_id": "$input.run_id"
          },
          "out": "runclose"
        },
        {
          "id": "status",
          "primitive": "derive-run-status",
          "version": "v1",
          "in": {
            "path_events": "$runpath.path_events",
            "finalized": "$runclose.finalized"
          },
          "out": "status"
        }
      ],
      "outcome_from": "runst",
      "route": {
        "default": {
          "dose": "$runst.dose",
          "stage": "$runst.stage",
          "status": "$status.status"
        }
      }
    },
    {
      "name": "report_need",
      "trigger": {
        "kind": "endpoint",
        "ref": "report_need"
      },
      "_note": "deterministic — log need + pause run",
      "steps": [
        {
          "id": "pause",
          "primitive": "update-run-state",
          "version": "v1",
          "in": {
            "run_id": "$input.run_id",
            "need": "$input.need"
          }
        },
        {
          "id": "jrnl",
          "primitive": "append-journal",
          "version": "v1",
          "in": {
            "run_id": "$input.run_id",
            "event": {
              "const": "report_need"
            },
            "payload": "$input.need"
          }
        }
      ],
      "route": {
        "default": {
          "recorded": {
            "const": true
          }
        }
      }
    },
    {
      "name": "methodist",
      "trigger": {
        "kind": "endpoint",
        "ref": "methodist"
      },
      "_note": "Single-door dispatcher (§3.1). fetch-run-state → route-intent decides diagnose|checkpoint|ask from run_state + payload, then dispatches to that sub-procedure. PUBLISH-SAFETY: checkpoint fires ONLY when the payload carries an explicit submission_hash (route-intent never synthesizes it); an artifact WITHOUT submission_hash always routes to ask, never to checkpoint.",
      "steps": [
        {
          "id": "runst",
          "primitive": "fetch-run-state",
          "version": "v1",
          "in": {
            "run_id": "$input.run_id"
          },
          "out": "runst"
        },
        {
          "id": "route",
          "primitive": "route-intent",
          "version": "v1",
          "params": {
            "publish_signal": [
              {
                "field": "submission_hash"
              }
            ]
          },
          "in": {
            "run_state": "$runst",
            "payload": "$input.payload"
          },
          "out": "route",
          "dispatch": {
            "routes": {
              "diagnose": "diagnose",
              "checkpoint": "checkpoint",
              "ask": "ask"
            }
          }
        }
      ],
      "route": {}
    }
  ],
  "_non_model_channels": {
    "_note": "escalate + get_my_development are NON-model channels (framework §3), not carrier doors. Likely direct endpoint→primitive, no procedure needed; included minimally for completeness — confirm with Core whether they route through the interpreter or bypass it.",
    "get_my_development": [
      "fetch-dossier(credential_id) → dossier (pure DB read)"
    ],
    "escalate": [
      "append-journal + create-corrective-activity(issue,class) → ticket (no model)"
    ]
  },
  "_process": {
    "_note": "§12.1 process-layer VALUES (methodist-owned; 2e reads from the methodology object). run-derived `done` status = presence of a non-superseded `version_closeout` activity for the run (durable append-only marker emitted at the closeout-checkpoint GO; v1.8 — done no longer recomputes against a mutable table). The stable final-stage map lives as a git-constant in Core's one-time back-fill script, NOT here (final_stage_by_cycle removed v1.8). path_node_shapes = the field-sets of the typed path nodes. Process nodes are opaque/not content-addressed (§12.1); hash-scopes are NOT here. ⚠ NB: course_event + consult_event MERGED → ask_event — the single-door merge (in main) means the `ask` procedure journals a const `ask` event, so course/consult path-nodes no longer occur; ask_event carries the ask_out fields.",
    "path_node_shapes": {
      "dose_issued": {
        "dose_content": [
          "operations",
          "beacons",
          "expected_artifacts",
          "counters",
          "probe?",
          "unit?"
        ]
      },
      "checkpoint_go": [
        "quality_stamp",
        "methodology_adherence",
        "reasons",
        "tier_signal?",
        "patches?",
        "next_dose_ref?",
        "track_note"
      ],
      "checkpoint_return": [
        "methodology_adherence",
        "reasons",
        "corrections",
        "tier_signal?",
        "patches?",
        "track_note"
      ],
      "ask_event": [
        "answer",
        "dose_adjustment?"
      ],
      "report_need": [
        "need"
      ]
    }
  }
}